mlflex.dataprocessors
Class RandomDataProcessor

java.lang.Object
  mlflex.dataprocessors.AbstractDataProcessor
      mlflex.dataprocessors.RandomDataProcessor

public class RandomDataProcessor
extends AbstractDataProcessor

This data processor generates data randomly. It is used for negative testing (ensuring that no positive result is attained when none is expected).

Author:
Stephen Piccolo

Constructor Detail

RandomDataProcessor

public RandomDataProcessor(java.lang.Integer numInstances,
                           java.lang.Integer numDiscreteDataPoints,
                           java.lang.Integer numContinuousDataPoints)
This constructor allows the user to specify how many random instances should be generated and how many data points should be generated per data instance.

Parameters:
numInstances - Number of data instances for which random data should be generated.
numDiscreteDataPoints - Number of discrete data points for which data should be generated (the discrete data points are either "Value1" or "Value2")
numContinuousDataPoints - Number of continuous data points for which data should be generated (the data points come from a standard normal distrubution)

This constructor allows the user to specify how many random instances should be generated and how many data points should be generated per data instance.

Parameters:
numInstances - Number of data instances for which random data should be generated.
numDiscreteDataPoints - Number of discrete data points for which data should be generated (the discrete data points are either "Value1" or "Value2")
numContinuousDataPoints - Number of continuous data points for which data should be generated (the data points come from a standard normal distribution)
description - Description of this data set that can be used to identify it uniquely
